    "# Geometria dos Espa\u00e7os de Embedding em Sistemas de Recomenda\u00e7\u00e3o\n",
    "## An\u00e1lise Comparativa de GNNs e Transformers \u2014 BraSNAM 2026\n",
    "\n",
    "Notebook consolidado contendo **LightGCN**, **KGAT (com aten\u00e7\u00e3o TransR)** e **SASRec (full-corpus eval)** para o artigo aceito no BraSNAM 2026.\n",
    "\n",
    "> Marinho, A. A.; Pedronette, D. C. G. *Geometria dos Embeddings em Recomenda\u00e7\u00e3o: GNNs e Transformers sob Manifold Learning.* XV BraSNAM, 2026.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Estrutura\n",
    "\n",
    "| Se\u00e7\u00e3o | Conte\u00fado |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| **1** | Setup e configura\u00e7\u00e3o (imports, device, seeds, paths) |\n",
    "| **2** | Download e prepara\u00e7\u00e3o dos datasets (ML-1M, Yelp2018, Amazon-Book) |\n",
    "| **3** | M\u00e9tricas (HR, Recall, NDCG full-corpus + NP/LDD geom\u00e9tricas) |\n",
    "| **4** | LightGCN (dataset, modelo, treino) |\n",
    "| **5** | KGAT com mecanismo de aten\u00e7\u00e3o (dataset, modelo, treino) |\n",
    "| **6** | SASRec com avalia\u00e7\u00e3o full-corpus (dataset, modelo, treino) |\n",
    "| **7** | An\u00e1lise geom\u00e9trica e visualiza\u00e7\u00e3o t-SNE |\n",
    "| **8** | Helpers de pipeline (agrega\u00e7\u00e3o por seed, save/load, hiperpar\u00e2metros) |\n",
    "| **9** | Smoke test (rodar primeiro para verificar fia\u00e7\u00e3o) |\n",
    "| **10** | Experimentos principais (Tabelas A, B, C) |\n",
    "| **11** | Consolida\u00e7\u00e3o Amazon-Book (merge dos JSONs por seed) |\n",
    "\n",
    "### Protocolos experimentais\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Tabela A \u2014 next-item prediction**: divis\u00e3o cronol\u00f3gica leave-one-out, eval full-corpus, **apenas ML-1M**, tr\u00eas modelos.\n",
    "- **Tabela B \u2014 recomenda\u00e7\u00e3o geral**: divis\u00e3o aleat\u00f3ria 80/20, eval full-corpus, **tr\u00eas datasets**, LightGCN e KGAT.\n",
    "- **Tabela C \u2014 geometria**: NP@10 e LDD@10 com **grafo de intera\u00e7\u00e3o como refer\u00eancia**.\n",
    "\n",
    "Todos os experimentos usam **3 seeds** (2020, 2021, 2022) e reportam **m\u00e9dia \u00b1 desvio padr\u00e3o**.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Como rodar\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Primeira vez:** suba o notebook no Colab com GPU \u2192 executa as Se\u00e7\u00f5es 1 a 8 (defini\u00e7\u00f5es) \u2192 executa o **smoke test** (Se\u00e7\u00e3o 9) para validar a fia\u00e7\u00e3o \u2192 come\u00e7a a Se\u00e7\u00e3o 10.\n",
    "2. **Em re-runs:** os experimentos checam se o JSON de sa\u00edda j\u00e1 existe e pulam (resume logic). Para for\u00e7ar re-execu\u00e7\u00e3o, defina `FORCE_OVERWRITE = True` no in\u00edcio da Se\u00e7\u00e3o 10.\n",
    "3. **Amazon-Book est\u00e1 em 3 cells separados** \u2014 Colab costuma crashar em runs longos; rodar um seed por vez \u00e9 mais seguro. A Se\u00e7\u00e3o 11 consolida os 3 JSONs no final.\n",
    "\n",
  },
